# Marketing site — canonical source

**Production truth:** [https://coop-ai.dev](https://coop-ai.dev) (deployed from `main`).

When editing the homepage, hero, or marketing demos, use the **current** light-theme stack — not legacy dark-theme components.

## Current homepage hero (production)

| Piece | File |
|-------|------|
| Hero layout | `website/src/components/Hero.tsx` → `<HeroDemoArtifact />` |
| 4 demo artefacts | `website/src/components/HeroDemoArtifact.tsx` |
| Site copy | `website/src/lib/site.config.ts` |
| Light theme | `website/src/app/layout.tsx` (`className` without `dark`), `website/tailwind.config.ts` |

Demo flow labels: `// question` → `// pulling context from` → `// context found` → `// response`.

## Legacy — do NOT treat as production homepage

| Legacy | File | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| Dark VS Code mock carousel | `website/src/components/FileContextStoryDemo.tsx` | `/file-context-demo` preview only |
| Old hero mock | `website/src/components/HeroProductMock.tsx` | Unused on production hero |
| Product page carousel | `website/src/components/ProductShowcaseCarousel.tsx` | `/product` only |

Before changing hero demo behavior, **confirm `Hero.tsx` imports `HeroDemoArtifact`**, not `FileContextStoryDemo`.

## Branch drift

Feature branches may lag `main` on `website/` (missing `HeroDemoArtifact.tsx`, old `Hero.tsx`). If local preview looks wrong:

1. Compare: `git diff main -- website/src/components/Hero.tsx`
2. Restore from main: `git checkout main -- website/` (or merge `main` into your branch)
3. Restart dev server after checkout

## Local preview

| Step | Detail |
|------|--------|
| Port | **3001** — `website/package.json` → `"dev": "next dev -p 3001"` |
| URL | `http://localhost:3001` (not 3000) |
| Command | `cd website && npm run dev` |
| Success | Light background, centered hero, `// response` box with 4 carousel dots |

Never point users at `localhost:3000` for the marketing site unless they explicitly started Next on that port.
